In the fleeting window of opportunity afforded by the clone's momentary disorientation, Albino acted with decisive brutality. His hands shot out, gripping the sides of the clone's head with an ironclad intensity. Muscles tensed and sinews strained as he applied a crushing force, the kind that could warp metal or crumple iron under normal circumstances. The intent was clear: to end the confrontation by caving in the clone's skull, a direct and final measure to neutralize the threat it posed.
Yet, the outcome was not as Albino anticipated. The clone's skull, reinforced by the same serum-enhanced resilience that fortified Albino's own body, withstood the pressure.
